CALL_START_FAILED

public static final int CALL_START_FAILED
Event code, indicating that a call has failed. The source will contain the session ID (if available), and the info field that contains the cause, which may be any one of the following:
JibeSessionEvent.INFO_USER_UNKNOWN
JibeSessionEvent.INFO_SESSION_TIMEOUT
JibeSessionEvent.INFO_USER_NOT_ONLINE
JibeSessionEvent.INFO_SESSION_REJECTED
JibeSessionEvent.INFO_SESSION_CANCELLED
JibeSessionEvent.INFO_RESOURCE_UNAVAILABLE

INFO_ADD_VIDEO_SEND

public static final int INFO_ADD_VIDEO_SEND
Flag indicating that the remote party wants to additionally send video to you in the context of an existing call. This flag can occur in the info of CALL_UPDATE_RECEIVED events. Refer to CallMediaInfo for more convenient handling of the update flags.

See Also:
Constant Field Values

public static final int INFO_ADD_VIDEO_RECEIVE
Flag indicating that the remote party wants to additionally receive video from you in the context of an existing call. This flag can occur in the info of CALL_UPDATE_RECEIVED events. Refer to CallMediaInfo for more convenient handling of the update flags.
